      {
        "id": "330ccf8821eaba356ba2395ed7723744f9017f95",
        "author": {
          "account_id": 481,
          "name": "Jessica Wagantall",
          "display_name": null,
          "email": "jwagantall@linuxfoundation.org",
          "username": "jwagantall"
        },
        "author_role": "OWNER",
        "timestamp": "2019-11-19 21:07:30.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 3:\n\nThanks for the review guys, as you can see in the sandbox, we need to make sure we are not using \"sonar-maven-plugin\" locally or through oparent. The discussion is happening here https://wiki.onap.org/display/DW/SonarCloud+migration+from+SonarQube",
        "patchset_number": 3
      },
      {
        "id": "ee6cb2aa82949261429f038803ae2cf572fc48bf",
        "author": {
          "account_id": 2787,
          "name": "Liam Fallon",
          "display_name": null,
          "email": "liam.fallon@est.tech",
          "username": "liamfallon"
        },
        "author_role": "REVIEWER",
        "timestamp": "2019-11-21 10:21:37.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 3:\n\nLooks like we are not using that plugin.\n\n~/git/onap/policy$ ls\napex-pdp  api  common  distribution  drools-applications  drools-pdp  engine  engine-orig  models  pap  parent  xacml-pdp\n~/git/onap/policy$ find . -name pom.xml -exec grep -i sonar-maven {} \\; -print | wc\n      0       0       0",
        "patchset_number": 3
      },
      {
        "id": "a22dd1bab2d8c5a3aef9b2e08f6b0162ca194747",
        "author": {
          "account_id": 57,
          "name": "Pamela Dragosh",
          "display_name": null,
          "email": "pd1248@att.com",
          "username": "pdragosh"
        },
        "author_role": "REVIEWER",
        "timestamp": "2019-11-21 12:25:10.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 3:\n\n> Patch Set 3:\n> \n> Looks like we are not using that plugin.\n> \n> ~/git/onap/policy$ ls\n> apex-pdp  api  common  distribution  drools-applications  drools-pdp  engine  engine-orig  models  pap  parent  xacml-pdp\n> ~/git/onap/policy$ find . -name pom.xml -exec grep -i sonar-maven {} \\; -print | wc\n>       0       0       0\n\nYep - you should be good to go with this step Jessica.",
        "patchset_number": 3
      },
      {
        "id": "1997f9de5e8f157733a3c99f847d02b59aef7d08",
        "author": {
          "account_id": 481,
          "name": "Jessica Wagantall",
          "display_name": null,
          "email": "jwagantall@linuxfoundation.org",
          "username": "jwagantall"
        },
        "author_role": "OWNER",
        "timestamp": "2019-11-21 18:59:36.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 3:\n\nBefore I proceeded, I ran one of these jobs as a test:\nhttps://jenkins.onap.org/job/policy-api-sonar/558/console\n\nNotice that the plugin is being inherited still which is failing since it calls SonarQube:\n\n10:55:57 [ERROR] Failed to execute goal org.sonarsource.scanner.maven:sonar-maven-plugin:3.2:sonar (default-cli) on project policy-api: Unable to execute SonarQube: Fail to download libraries from server: 1 -> [Help 1]\n\nIs this being inherited from oparent maybe?",
        "patchset_number": 3
      },
      {
        "id": "79dd8a9180beb450e0b21a6746915e3b5304e9b5",
        "author": {
          "account_id": 57,
          "name": "Pamela Dragosh",
          "display_name": null,
          "email": "pd1248@att.com",
          "username": "pdragosh"
        },
        "author_role": "REVIEWER",
        "timestamp": "2019-11-21 22:18:45.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 3:\n\n> Patch Set 3:\n> \n> Before I proceeded, I ran one of these jobs as a test:\n> https://jenkins.onap.org/job/policy-api-sonar/558/console\n> \n> Notice that the plugin is being inherited still which is failing since it calls SonarQube:\n> \n> 10:55:57 [ERROR] Failed to execute goal org.sonarsource.scanner.maven:sonar-maven-plugin:3.2:sonar (default-cli) on project policy-api: Unable to execute SonarQube: Fail to download libraries from server: 1 -> [Help 1]\n> \n> Is this being inherited from oparent maybe?\n\nWe overwrite oparent pluginManagement (its settings are in oparent/integration/pom.xml) - because we need to aggregate our reports and oparent settings do not do that by default.",
        "patchset_number": 3
      },
      {
        "id": "7fc23a8d68a0ec9caaa4f53b4654525d97e364b5",
        "author": {
          "account_id": 481,
          "name": "Jessica Wagantall",
          "display_name": null,
          "email": "jwagantall@linuxfoundation.org",
          "username": "jwagantall"
        },
        "author_role": "OWNER",
        "timestamp": "2019-11-21 22:53:47.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 3:\n\nThanks Pam!.. I am still puzzled on where is this being called from.. However, I got some news. Seems that this plugin does not need to be removed after all, but rather we need to upgrade its version to this one:\nhttps://sonarcloud.io/documentation/analysis/scan/sonarscanner-for-maven/\n\nAs example, we can see VID passes using the same plugin but with the 3.6 version: https://jenkins.onap.org/view/vid/job/vid-sonar/693/\n\nIf I could know where can we set the version for this plugin, we could probably just change it and try again",
        "patchset_number": 3
      },
      {
        "id": "7d37b9293c57fd3ac295f9e0ed6afb9c00df0b57",
        "author": {
          "account_id": 481,
          "name": "Jessica Wagantall",
          "display_name": null,
          "email": "jwagantall@linuxfoundation.org",
          "username": "jwagantall"
        },
        "author_role": "OWNER",
        "timestamp": "2019-11-21 23:43:43.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 3:\n\n@Pam, I actually figured out a way to force the 3.6 version of the plugin. I basically changed the goal to \"org.sonarsource.scanner.maven:sonar-maven-plugin:3.6.0.1398:sonar\" in the job template:\nhttps://jenkins.onap.org/job/policy-api-sonar/563/\n\nThis worked and generated a report. Can you please let me know how it looks to you?\nhttps://sonarcloud.io/dashboard?id=onap_policy-api",
        "patchset_number": 3
      },
      {
        "id": "d024f198b8e9caaf2716afdf4c979b0953d34849",
        "author": {
          "account_id": 57,
          "name": "Pamela Dragosh",
          "display_name": null,
          "email": "pd1248@att.com",
          "username": "pdragosh"
        },
        "author_role": "REVIEWER",
        "timestamp": "2019-11-22 14:28:33.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 3:\n\n> Patch Set 3:\n> \n> @Pam, I actually figured out a way to force the 3.6 version of the plugin. I basically changed the goal to \"org.sonarsource.scanner.maven:sonar-maven-plugin:3.6.0.1398:sonar\" in the job template:\n> https://jenkins.onap.org/job/policy-api-sonar/563/\n> \n> This worked and generated a report. Can you please let me know how it looks to you?\n> https://sonarcloud.io/dashboard?id=onap_policy-api\n\nYes it looks fine",
        "patchset_number": 3
      },
